<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,334,1104,1130]" box="[189,334,1104,1130]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1104,1130]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1104,1130]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[187,1400,1151,1424]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Test shape elongate cylindrical and slender; distinctly curved, slightly nodular, and evenly tapering in a rounded but narrow end. Length of test 
<quantity box="[697,799,1187,1213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
, the longest is 
<quantity box="[983,1078,1186,1213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
; test width 
<quantity box="[1220,1396,1186,1213]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="0.2" valueMax="0.25" valueMin="0.15">0.15–0.25 mm</quantity>
. Chambers initially cylindrical, becoming slightly inflated and more elongated as added. Chamber arrangement rectilinear, minimal embracement; number of chambers commonly 6–11, or up to 14. Initial chambers in microsphere are rectilinear. Sutures oblique. Aperture radial, nearly central and usually protruding, with up to 16 symmetrically arranged tines that are fused in the center. Surface smooth without ornamentation; secondary surface laminations absent (atelo-lamellar). Wall finely perforated, thin, and transparent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,303,1463,1489]" box="[189,303,1463,1489]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1463,1489]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1463,1489]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[189,1398,1510,1607]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Of the 24 examined specimens, 14 had an intact initial end, with prolocular size that varied nearly continuously from less than 0.05 to about 
<quantity box="[726,840,1545,1571]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
, presumably including both generations with rectilinear chamber arrangement of the initial part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
